- The performance score of a car is calculated based on the evaluation criteria scores obtained from various evaluators; 
- Higher scores indicate better performance; 
- The ranking is based on the total score of the top evaluation for each car.

- The car evaluation data contains various attributes and scores obtained from multiple evaluators; 
- The ranking and quartile assignment help identify the best cars within each manufacturer and overall, respectively; 
- The average, minimum, and maximum scores provide a comprehensive understanding of a car's evaluation.
